'''William Neville''' (15 May 1935 – 29 September 2018) was an Irish [[Association football|footballer]] from [[Cork (city)|Cork]] who played as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]] for [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]].
==Career== Neville played five games for West Ham in the 1957–58 season before being invalided out of the game, aged 22 with [[tuberculosis]]. He died on 29 September 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.whufc.com/news/articles/2018/october/03-october/billy-neville-1935-2018|title=Billy Neville&nbsp;– 1935-2018 - West Ham United|website=www.whufc.com|accessdate=3 October 2018}}</ref><ref name="westhamstats">{{cite web|url=http://wwwd.westhamstats.info/westham.php?west=2&ham=496&united=Billy_Neville|website=wwwd.westhamstats.info|title=Billy Neville West Ham United stats|accessdate=3 October 2018}}</ref>
