[[File:HootGibson.jpg|thumb|alt=Hoot Gibson|Hoot Gibson (c. 1924)]] This is a complete filmography of American actor [[Hoot Gibson]] (August 6, 1892 – August 23, 1962), including his performances between 1910 and 1960. Gibson appeared in more than 200 films.
==Background== Gibson's career began in 1910 with early [[silent film]] "[[short film|shorts]]", and he continued as a movie star once "[[talkies]]" were introduced, his first sound film being ''The Long, Long Trail'' (1929).<ref>[https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0020107/trivia IMDb: ''The Long, Long Trail'' trivia]</ref> Primarily starring in [[Western (genre)|Western]] films, Gibson worked with many directors, including [[John Ford]], who would direct many popular American Westerns and [[American Civil War|Civil War]] films, over his fifty years of film production, including ''The Horse Soldiers'' (1959), starring [[John Wayne]], in which Gibson played a supporting role. As with many silent and early recordings, a number of Gibson's films are considered to be [[lost film|lost]]. {{clear}}
