{{Infobox person | name = Patricia Kihoro | image = | caption = | birth_name = Patricia Wangechi Kihoro | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1986|1|4}} | birth_place = [[Nairobi]], Kenya | home_town = | nationality = [[Kenyan]] | citizenship = | occupation = {{flat list| * [[Singer-songwriter]] * [[actress]] * [[radio presenter]] }} | years_active = 2004–present | spouse = | partner = |children = | net_worth = <!-- Do NOT change to Celebrity Net Worth, which is not a reliable source --> | module = {{Infobox musical artist | embed = yes | background = solo_singer | genre = {{flat list| *[[R&B]]<ref name="Party">{{cite web|url=https://www.reverbnation.com/patriciakihoro|title=Reverbnation: Patricia Kihoro|accessdate=1 February 2015|website=Reverbnation}}</ref> * {{nowrap|[[Pop music|pop]]<ref name="Party" />}} *{{nowrap|[[Soul music|soul]]<ref name="Party" />}} *{{nowrap|[[neo soul]]<ref name="Party" />}}}} }} | label_name = | website = {{URL|http://www.patriciakihoro.com}} }}
'''Patricia Wangechi Kihoro''' (born 4 January 1986)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mashada.com/blogs/p/231658/kenya-s3xy-homeboyz-radio-presenter-patricia-kihoro-reveals-her-age-and-leaves-many-surprised-picture|title=S3xy Homeboyz Radio presenter Patricia Kihoro reveals her age and leaves many surprised!|accessdate=1 February 2016|website=Mashada}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://worldofbigbrother.com/Academy/Afr/T3/Patricia.shtml|title=Patricia Wangechi Kihoro profile|accessdate=1 February 2016|website=World of Big Brother}}</ref> is a Kenyan singer, songwriter, actress, radio and reality television personality. She rose into prominence after she participated in the third season of ''[[Tusker Project Fame]]'', where she became one of the finalists. In acting, she has appeared in a number of local productions like the 2011 film, ''Miss Nobody'', which saw her being nominated in the 2012 [[Kalasha Awards]] for best lead actress in a film. In television production, she has been cast as a lead in ''Groove Theory'', a musical drama and as a regular in ''Demigods'', ''Changes'', ''[[Rush (2014 Kenyan TV series)|Rush]]'' and ''[[Makutano Junction]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.talenteastafrica.com/2015/06/patricia-kihoro.html?m=1|title=Patricia Kihoro|accessdate=5 February 2016|website=Talent East Africa}}</ref> As a radio presenter, she has worked with One FM and Homeboyz FM.<ref>{{cite web|author=Chrysanthus Ikeh|url=http://thenet.ng/2014/02/patricia-kihoro-to-host-shows-with-homeboyz-radio-103-5/|title=Patricia Kihoro to host shows with Homeboyz Radio 103.5|accessdate=5 February 2016|website=The Net}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://nairobiwire.com/2014/02/patricia-kihoro-lands-radio-show-two-year-wait.html|title=Patricia Kihoro Lands New Radio Job|accessdate=5 February 2016|website=Nairobi Wire}}</ref>
== Early life == Kihoro, born in January 1986 and raised in Kenya's capital [[Nairobi]], attended Shepherd’s Junior Primary School for her primary school and later moved on to Moi Girls' High School, Nairobi. After her O levels, she enrolled in [[Moi University]] in the school of Science and psychology. While in Moi University, she opted to audition for the third season of ''[[Tusker Project Fame]]''.<ref>{{cite web|date=23 September 2015|first=|last=|url=http://www.sde.co.ke/m/article/2000177337/wcw-patricia-kihoro-rising-to-the-top-of-kenyan-showbiz-industry|title= Patricia Kihoro-Rising to the top of Kenyan showbiz industry|accessdate=3 February 2016|website=SDE}}</ref>
== Career ==
=== 2009{{ndash}}12 === In March 2009, Kihoro auditioned for the reality singing competition ''[[Tusker Project Fame]]'' . In 2011 she played Pet Nanjala in drama series ''Changes''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kenyabuzz.com/lifestyle/patricia-kihoro-profile|title=HOT: Patricia Kihoro|accessdate=3 February 2016|website=Kenya Buzz}}</ref> The same year she played in a leading role in film, ''Miss Nobody'' that led her to be nominated in the 2011 Kalasha Awards for lead actress in film category. In the 2012, she was cast as one of the leads in [[Musical drama film|musical drama]] ''Groove Theory''. She portrayed Biscuit, Zamm's (portrayed by Kevin Maina) in a story that revoled among five a fictional Victoria University students.<ref>{{cite web|date=4 December 2013|url=http://www.actors.co.ke/en/mer/articledetail/487|title=KENYA’S 1ST MUSICAL TV DRAMA SERIES- THE GROOVE THEORY|accessdate=3 February 2016|website=Actors.co.ke}}</ref>
=== 2013{{ndash}}14=== In 2013 she appeared in reality show ''The Fattening Room'',<ref>{{cite web|date=28 April 2013|first=Oluwafunke|last=Lasisi|url=http://www.thisdaylive.com/articles/ebonylife-brings-six-african-ladies-to-the-fattening-room/146139/|title=EbonyLife Brings Six African Ladies to The Fattening Room|accessdate=5 February 2016|website=This Day Live}}{{dead link|date=March 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> that led her fellow cast members and she to explore the customs and traditions of [[Efik people]] in south-east Nigeria.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ebonylifetv.com/programming/ebonylife-homegrown/reality/fattening-room/|title=Fattening Room|accessdate=5 February 2016|website=Ebony Life TV }}</ref> In 2014, she was cast (2012) as Nana, a 28 year old editor in the series, ''[[Rush (2014 Kenyan TV series)|Rush]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://intheloopkenya.blogspot.co.ke/2012/04/rush-kenya-version-of-sex-and-city-to.html?m=0|title=Rush; Kenyas version of sex and city|accessdate=5 February 2016|website=In The Loop}}</ref> She played alongside Janet Mbugua, Wendy Kimani, Wendy Sankale and Maryanne Nundo.<ref>{{cite web|date=18 April 2012|author=Baba Ghafla|url=http://www.ghafla.co.ke/news/music/1205-rush-new-tv-series-coming-soon-packed-with-celebs|title=Rush: New TV series packed with celebs|accessdate=5 February 2016|website=Ghafla!}}</ref>
=== 2015{{ndash}}present === In 2015, she was cast as [[Maqbul Mohammed]]'s daughter in series, ''[[Makutano Junction]]''.
