{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2012}} {{Infobox football biography | name = Salah Assad | image = Assad, salah 1986.jpg | fullname = Salah Assad | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1958|03|13|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Larbaâ Nath Irathen]], [[Algeria]] | height = 1.84 m | position = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]] | youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = | years1 = 1975–1982 | clubs1 = [[RC Kouba]] | caps1 = – | goals1 = – | years2 = 1982–1983 | clubs2 = [[FC Mulhouse]] | caps2 = 26 | goals2 = 13 | years3 = 1983–1984 | clubs3 = [[Paris Saint-Germain Football Club|Paris SG]] | caps3 = 9 | goals3 = 1 | years4 = 1985–1986 | clubs4 = [[FC Mulhouse]] | caps4 = 55 | goals4 = 15 | years5 = 1986–1989 | clubs5 = [[RC Kouba]] | caps5 = – | goals5 = – | years6 = 1989 | clubs6 = [[JSM Chéraga]] | caps6 = – | goals6 = – | nationalyears1 = 1978–1989 | nationalteam1 = [[Algeria national football team|Algeria]] | nationalcaps1 = 68 | nationalgoals1 = 18 }}
'''Salah Assad''' ({{lang-ar|صالح عصاد}}; born 10 June 1958 in [[Larbaâ Nath Irathen]]) is a former [[Algeria]]n [[Association football|football]] striker and manager.
He played for [[RC Kouba]], where he won an Algerian tournament in 1981 and one African Cup Winner's Cup, and in France for [[FC Mulhouse]] and [[Paris Saint-Germain FC]]. For [[Algeria national football team]], he participated at the [[1980 African Cup of Nations|1980]], [[1982 African Cup of Nations|1982]], and [[1986 African Cup of Nations]], [[1980 Summer Olympics]],<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Sports Reference|title=Salah Assad Biography and Statistics|url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/as/salah-assad-1.html|accessdate=2009-07-13}}</ref> and at two edition of [[FIFA World Cup]] in [[1982 FIFA World Cup|1982]] and [[1986 FIFA World Cup|1986]], scored two goals.
Assad currently holds the record of most scored goals at the World Cup for Algeria, which were both scored in the 1982 World Cup.<ref>http://soccernet.espn.go.com/worldcup2010/team/history/_/id/624/algeria?cc=5739&ver=globa</ref>
==Honours==
=== Club === * [[Algerian Championnat National|Algerian League]] Champion in 1981 with [[RC Kouba]]
=== International === * Gold medal in the [[1978 All-Africa Games]] in [[Algiers]] * Bronze medal in the [[1979 Mediterranean Games]] in [[Split (city)|Split]] * 2nd in the final of the [[1980 African Cup of Nations]] in Nigeria * Quarter final round in the [[1980 Summer Olympics]] Games in Moscow * 2 participations in [[FIFA World Cup]] of [[1982 FIFA World Cup|1982]] in Spain & [[1986 FIFA World Cup|1986]] in Mexico
== Individual == * [[Africa Cup of Nations]] Team of the Tournament:[[1980 African Cup of Nations|1980,]][[1982 African Cup of Nations|1982]] * Best left forward in [[1982 FIFA World Cup]] * Best African sportsman in 1982 * 2nd best African football player in 1982
